//----------------------------------------------------------------------------\\
                        HTTP

.   The primary function of a web server is to store, process, and deliver web pages to
        clients. The communication between client and server takes place using the Hypertext
        Transfer Protocol (HTTP).


HTTP :
    is built on top of TCP (transmission control Protocl)

HTTP : communication protocol used by WEB APIS (Application Programming Interface)
    the protocol follows a client server model, where clients communicate with servers by
    sending requests and waiting for responses.
    one of the most important properties of http requests is the request method
    called the http verbs

            //+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\\
                        GET (GET)
        request Method = Get
    . simple requests for infromation
    . should only retrieve(get back) data 
    . shouldn't result in modification of data

                Get employee information ----->(Get)-----> Employees API

            //+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\\
                        POST (CREATE)
    . Modify the underlying data (modify the state of the underlying data)
    . create new resources (meaning whenever a new employee is hired by out company
        we woulf send a post request to the employee's endpoint to add a new employee
        resource)

            //+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\\
                        DELETE
    . Remove existing resources (whenever an employee leaves our company we might send
        a delete request to the employee api to remove the employee from our systems )

